I think I would be good. They are using the ace text editor, so something simple like:<p>on pageload:
var t = localStorage.getItem(&quot;textbackup&quot;);
if (t){
	__editor.setValue(t);
	console.log(&#x27;restoring from backup&#x27;);
} else {
	__editor.setValue(document.getElementById(&#x27;basic_intro&#x27;).innerHTML);
	console.log(&#x27;putting in the intro&#x27;);
}<p>and on any action:
var text = __editor.getValue();
localStorage.setItem(&#x27;textbackup&#x27;, text);<p>It&#x27;s the approach I&#x27;ve taken in my version a playground for a different program.
